            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Debouncing `on_win` could alleviate the flickering issue because it reduces the frequency of extmark clear/set.\n\nBut the flicker comes from exposing the intermediate state between where refreshed lenses are being resolved.\nEven with debouncing, the final call still has to decide what to do for unresolved lenses.\nIf it clears the existing extmark at that point, users can still see flicker.\n\nTo avoid that, we need to keep the previously rendered extmark visible until the refreshed lens is resolved, and only then replace it atomically in a single redraw step. That is what this PR does.\n",
            "commit_id": "c32627dcecc4b423acbf6554bf7bc13dd24e141d",
            "created_at": "2026-04-06T15:59:01Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -222,16 +222,29 @@ end\n ---@param toprow integer\n ---@param botrow integer\n function Provider:on_win(toprow, botrow)",
