        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> > This feature is on my roadmap, but I haven't figured out a good way to implement it yet. Looking at the code, I have some concerns about the current PR's implementation; it seems to have too much logic interspersed in various places.\n> \n> \n> \n> @ofseed is \"your roadmap\" documented somewhere? Else it might be unclear to other contributors what exactly you're planning on tackling and how.\n\nThank you for the suggestion. I will open a tracking issue for this kind of case in the future. I only have a few vague ideas at the moment without any concrete approach yet, and I do not mean that this should become a blocker for other contributors.\n\nSo my main concern is that, personally, I am not very satisfied with some of the implementation choices here. For example, this newly added loop at the top of `on_win` appears to run in all cases, which means that even a viewport movement with no text change at all, such as moving up by one line, would still iterate over all extmarks in a buffer. By contrast, our existing caching mechanism only ever traverses the visible lines in the buffer, and it only operates on a line after that line’s content has changed; otherwise, it skips it directly. As a result, the performance hotspot would shift to the loop above.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-07T02:03:59Z",
